The White House Office of the Press Secretary released a readout of a meeting between National Security Advisor Tom Donilon and Indian National Security Advisor Shivshankar Menon. The meeting was held to follow up on the outcomes of President Obama and Indian Prime Minister Singh's Summit in India in November 2010. They discussed ways to advance the bilateral agenda, including implementing initiatives launched during the Summit and building new platforms for collaboration. The two also had discussions on regional and global issues of mutual concern. President Obama joined the meeting and expressed his commitment to building a global strategic partnership with India. He also shared his priorities for the coming year, which include advancing the bilateral economic relationship and making progress on nuclear security efforts.